"I am open to career change. I'm curious. I think creating and testing jelly bean flavors would be fun. I think you are brave. I watched a video about it. I have a pitch for you when you start working there. I wonder what the sound of a flute tastes like. I think flute music is soothing. I think we can do buisness our selves. I believe in the ""universe"". I need to make money. I don't need the money. I care about children with disabilities.","Oh really? What would that be? I always have my eyes open for career change opportunities. I saw a job that involved creating and testing new jelly bean flavors!  That would be kinda fun! Well, in the video I saw, they have like a giant storeroom full of every flavoring known to man, and a masterbook of recipes that combine to make different basic flavors.  Basically they just think up stuff, and then tweak the standard recipe until they are satisfied and then test it.  I wonder if they can make tastes based on smells of things that one doesn't usually taste. And I wonder if they make tastes that imitate sounds. You know, abstract mixing of the senses in an artistic way. Would you pitch it to them when you start working there for me? Sure! But I probably had better come up with a few winners first before I go to far into the breach! haha.  It's an intriguing idea though. Like, what would the sound of a flute taste like? Exactly! And you could box it in a way that when they open the box, a flute song plays. And they basically eat jelly beans to soothing flute music. It could be really cool for children with sensory development issues. Wow! Maybe you and I should just go into the jelly bean business for ourselves! lol You live on a farm, so we'd have access to plenty of corn syrup! haha How about renting it instead of giving it away?  I do need to make some money!  You can totally be the contact person with Jelly Bean company. Sell the idea to them and donate my portion to some autism foundation. ",test_123_4
